parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the battery to drain, leading to a loss of power and potentially leaving the driver stranded. In extreme cases, it can also cause the electrical system to malfunction, which can lead to accidents.

The failure of the battery can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leaving the driver stranded. This can also lead to a loss of power to critical systems, such as the brakes and steering, which can increase the risk of accidents.
The failure of the air conditioner can cause discomfort and distraction for the driver and passengers, potentially leading to heat-related health issues or accidents.

the air conditioner is not working
the air conditioner is not cooling
the air conditioner is leaking refrigerant
